Text: China strolled in like he owned the place—oh wait, he kinda does.
Meanwhile, Taiwan was all “can I join?
” as I rolled my eyes so hard I almost saw my past freedoms.
I tried to explain the whole “one country, two systems” thing, but my umbrella got in the way during my dramatic twirl.
Guam chimed in about some new defense plans—can't blame her for wanting a little safety.
Anyway, I ducked out for some dim sum, because who has time for geopolitics when there’s steamed buns to enjoy?
